12. Multivariate Distance Using Bray Curtis

  • Show All Code
  • Hide All Code
  • View Source
Author

Colin J Lee

We want to calculate the multivariate distance between two profiles, between and within-person. Bray-Curtis dissimilarity is an absolute distance metric, like Euclidian and Manhattan, but it can be decomposed into replacement (variables in one profile are higher and lower than another profile) and nestedness (one profileâs variables are uniformly higher or lower than another profile). At the between-level: we want to calculate the Bray-Curtis dissimilarity between a profile and the mean of the sampleâs aggregate profiles. i think? Within p: 1. B-C between a profileâs means and the mean of the participantâs time series 2. B-C between one profileâs means and another profileâs means (obv within person)

Between person: 1. distance matrix of profile means 2. a profileâs means and sample profile mean

within-person: 1. a profileâs mean and time series mean 2. a profileâs mean and another profileâs mean

typology: 1. profile mean and typology

#POMP
pomp <- function(x, min, max){
  (x - min)/(max - min)*100
} 

reserved_vec <- pomp(x = reserved_vec, min = 1, max = 5)
names(reserved_vec) <- c("Extraversion", "Agreeableness", "Conscientiousness", "Neuroticism_r", "Openness")

profile_plot_fnc <- function(df){
  df %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = facet, y = value, group = Profiles, color = Profiles)) +
    geom_line(linewidth = 1.25) +
    geom_point(size = 2.25, color = "black") +
    labs(x = NULL, y = "Self-Reported Score (POMP)") +
    ylim(0,103) +
    theme_bw(base_size = 8) +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1, size = 10), legend.position = "top") +
    labs(title = "Profiles With Maximum and Minimum Distances from PPS Facet Means") +
    #annotate("rect", xmin = 3.8, xmax = 6.2, ymin = 46, ymax = 93, fill = "green", alpha = .2) +
    #annotate("rect", xmin = 0.8, xmax = 3.2, ymin = 25, ymax = 77, fill = "red", alpha = .2) +
    geom_vline(xintercept = c(3.5, 6.5, 9.5, 12.5), size = 0.25, alpha = 0.8) +
    annotate("text", x = 2, y = 102, size = 2.5,label = "Extraversion") +
    annotate("text", x = 5, y = 102, size = 2.5,label = "Agreeableness") +
    annotate("text", x = 8, y = 102, size=  2.5, label = "Conscientiousness") +
    annotate("text", x = 11, y = 102, size = 2.5, label = "Emotional Stability") +
    annotate("text", x = 14, y = 102, size = 2.5, label = "Openness")
}

#aggregate into traits for typology comps
trait_fun <- function(df){
  df %>% 
    rowwise() %>%
    mutate(Extraversion = mean(c_across(Sociability:Assertive)),
           Agreeableness = mean(c_across(Trust:Compassion)),
           Conscientiousness = mean(c_across(Productivity:Organization)),
           Neuroticism_r = mean(c_across(Depression_r:EmotionalVol_r)),
           Openness = mean(c_across(IntCuriosity:CrtvImagination))
           ) %>%
    ungroup() %>%
    select(Extraversion:Openness)
}

pp_nested_traits <- pp_nested_profiles %>%
  mutate(trait_df = map(data, trait_fun),
         trait_mean = map(trait_df, colMeans),
         trait_mean = map(trait_mean, as.data.frame),
         trait_mean = map(trait_mean, t)) %>%
  select(SID, Profiles, trait_mean, trait_df) %>%
  mutate(trait_variance = map(trait_df, function(x) apply(x, 2, sd)))

#combine trait and typology vector and compute bray
pp_nested_traits_bcd <- pp_nested_traits %>%
  mutate(reserved_df = map2(reserved_list,
                            as.vector(pp_nested_traits$trait_mean), 
                            function(x,y) rbind(x,y)),
         excitable_df = map2(excitable_list,
                            as.vector(pp_nested_traits$trait_mean), 
                            function(x,y) rbind(x,y)),
         well_adj_df = map2(well_adj_list,
                            as.vector(pp_nested_traits$trait_mean), 
                            function(x,y) rbind(x,y))) %>%
  mutate(res_dist = map(reserved_df, bray.part), #distance matrix
         well_dist = map(well_adj_df, bray.part),
         exc_dist = map(excitable_df, bray.part))
save(pp_nested_traits_bcd, file = "Data/pp_nested_traits_bcd.RData")

We want to calculate the multivariate distance between two profiles, between and within-person. Bray-Curtis dissimilarity is an absolute distance metric, like Euclidian and Manhattan, but it can be decomposed into replacement (variables in one profile are higher *and* lower than another profile) and nestedness (one profile's variables are uniformly higher or lower than another profile). At the between-level: we want to calculate the Bray-Curtis dissimilarity between a profile and the mean of the sample's aggregate profiles. i think? Within p: 1. B-C between a profile's means and the mean of the participant's time series 2. B-C between one profile's means and another profile's means (obv within person)

Between person: 1. distance matrix of profile means 2. a profile's means and sample profile mean

within-person: 1. a profile's mean and time series mean 2. a profile's mean and another profile's mean

typology: 1. profile mean and typology

reserved_vec <- reserved_vec[index]
excitable_vec <- excitable_vec[index]

#POMP
pomp <- function(x, min, max){
  (x - min)/(max - min)*100
} 

reserved_vec <- pomp(x = reserved_vec, min = 1, max = 5)
names(reserved_vec) <- c("Extraversion", "Agreeableness", "Conscientiousness", "Neuroticism_r", "Openness")

names(well_adj_vec) <- c("Extraversion", "Agreeableness", "Conscientiousness", "Neuroticism_r", "Openness")
excitable_vec <- pomp(x = excitable_vec, min = 1 , max = 5)

#aggregate into traits for typology comps
trait_fun <- function(df){
  df %>% 
    rowwise() %>%
    mutate(Extraversion = mean(c_across(Sociability:Assertive)),
           Agreeableness = mean(c_across(Trust:Compassion)),
           Conscientiousness = mean(c_across(Productivity:Organization)),
           Neuroticism_r = mean(c_across(Depression_r:EmotionalVol_r)),
           Openness = mean(c_across(IntCuriosity:CrtvImagination))
           ) %>%
    ungroup() %>%
    select(Extraversion:Openness)
}

pp_nested_traits <- pp_nested_profiles %>%
  mutate(trait_df = map(data, trait_fun),
         trait_mean = map(trait_df, colMeans),
         trait_mean = map(trait_mean, as.data.frame),
         trait_mean = map(trait_mean, t)) %>%
  select(SID, Profiles, trait_mean, trait_df) %>%
  mutate(trait_variance = map(trait_df, function(x) apply(x, 2, sd)))

#combine trait and typology vector and compute bray
pp_nested_traits_bcd <- pp_nested_traits %>%
  mutate(reserved_df = map2(reserved_list,
                            as.vector(pp_nested_traits$trait_mean), 
                            function(x,y) rbind(x,y)),
         excitable_df = map2(excitable_list,
                            as.vector(pp_nested_traits$trait_mean), 
                            function(x,y) rbind(x,y)),
         well_adj_df = map2(well_adj_list,
                            as.vector(pp_nested_traits$trait_mean), 
                            function(x,y) rbind(x,y))) %>%
  mutate(res_dist = map(reserved_df, bray.part), #distance matrix
         well_dist = map(well_adj_df, bray.part),
         exc_dist = map(excitable_df, bray.part))
save(pp_nested_traits_bcd, file = "Data/pp_nested_traits_bcd.RData")
#extract estimates
typology_sample <- pp_nested_traits_bcd

#reserved estimates per profile
reserved_distance_vector <- list()
#so fucking stupid i had to for loop but map was killing me 
for(i in 1:nrow(typology_sample)){
    reserved_distance_vector[[i]] <- typology_sample$res_dist[[i]]$bray #first col
}

#well adj estimates per profile
well_adj_distance_vector <- list()
#so fucking stupid i had to for loop but map was killing me 
for(i in 1:nrow(typology_sample)){
    well_adj_distance_vector[[i]] <- typology_sample$well_dist[[i]]$bray #first col
}

#excitable
excitable_distance_vector <- list()
#so fucking stupid i had to for loop but map was killing me 
for(i in 1:nrow(typology_sample)){
    excitable_distance_vector[[i]] <- typology_sample$exc_dist[[i]]$bray #first col
}

bray_typ_wide <- data.frame(
  SID = typology_sample$SID, 
  Profiles = typology_sample$Profiles,
  Excitable = unlist(excitable_distance_vector),
  Reserved = unlist(reserved_distance_vector),
  WellAdj = unlist(well_adj_distance_vector)
  )
save(bray_typ_wide, file = "Data/bray_typ_wide.RData")

bray_typ <- bray_typ_wide %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = Excitable:WellAdj) %>%

         typology = name)
save(bray_typ, file = "Data/bray_typ.RData")

#overall bray
typology_bray_summary <- bray_typ %>%
  group_by(typology) %>%
  summarize(mean_distance = mean(mean, na.rm = TRUE),
            sd_distance = sd(mean, na.rm = TRUE))
